      "Damage survey conducted",
      "Witness statements taken"
    ],
    "summary": "On April 8, 2019 at approximately 0600 hours, a fire occurred in the Fire Box of Heater Treater (NBK-2900) on South Pelto Block 23 Platform D. Hydrocarbons leaked from cracks in the fire tube and contacted the burner flame due to insufficient tube support, causing ignition. The fire melted the aluminum fire box and activated the Burner Safety Low alarm. The fire was extinguished using a fire hose and hand held fire extinguisher. No injuries were reported. Estimated damage was $75,000.",
